swissarmyhammer-entity-search/src/fuzzy.rs:32-34

```rust
let text = match value.as_str() {
    Some(s) => s.to_string(),
    None => value.to_string(),
};
```

The `Some(s) => s.to_string()` branch allocates a new String from a `&str` only to pass it to `fuzzy_match` which accepts `&str`. The allocation is unnecessary for the common string-value case.

Suggestion: Use `Cow<str>` or restructure to avoid the allocation:
```rust
use std::borrow::Cow;
let text: Cow<str> = match value.as_str() {
    Some(s) => Cow::Borrowed(s),
    None => Cow::Owned(value.to_string()),
};
```
